We tried messing with the dial but nothing could get the fire hotter. Eventually a waiter came over and told us that they'd been having troubles with that grill so we could move to another table. At this point, we'd been there about an hour and had barely eaten so we moved and that grill worked a lot better. reviews.text:
I really like this chain of sushi and Japanese cuisine restaurants. On Sunday we tried to visit their location in Lynnwood, but it was completely full, so we decided to come here instead. The dishes were served quickly ‚Äî here the food is brought by a server, not a robot like in some of their other locations. The menu is similar to other restaurants in this chain. The portions are quite large: big pieces of fish, big rolls, and plenty of fish overall. We loved the self-serve bar. There were so many choices available and made it easy to grab things like ginger/wasabi/miso soup as needed. The self-serve thai tea with topping options was also a plus. Pretty solid spot for all-you-can-eat sushi near UW. Service was super friendly and quick, and the place felt clean, which is always a good sign.

The sashimi really makes it worth it! It tastes fresh and delicious. The rolls and sides were great too. The only downside I experienced was the walk up bar hot food was empty during the first half of my meal. Other than that, the drinks were decent, sauces were available, and the speed of food delivery was quick. I will definitely come back again and recommend to my friends!

Might be a bit overhyped. It's a good value for all-you-can-eat, but the quality of the food is hit or miss. The rolls were pretty impressive, but everything else (including the sashimi) seemed pretty cheap and padded with rice to fill you up. Don't waste your stomach on the ramen or other side dishes.

reviews.text: My fiance and I have been coming here every couple months for a few years and it is fantastic every time. It‚Äôs our favorite restaurant in Seattle. Village Sushi is in a modest spot on the north end of University Way. reviews.text: Wife and I decided to check this spot out for lunch on New Year's Day. Because of the timing and how early we went, parking was easily found down the street. We were immediately greeted with smiles and hellos and the smell of DELICIOUS food! The staff was so friendly! reviews.text:
$14.99 per lb. Plenty of options to fill your bowl. Bone broth 2 star was what and my girlfriend ordered. It wasn‚Äôt too hot but very tasty.

Went to this restaurant style in Shanghai and so glad I can have it again in Seattle. You pick and choose your own ingredients so you can't go wrong with dietary restrictions. The soup base choices are clearly labeled and their beef broth was awesome. Ordered spicy level 2 and it was ok for people who eat spicy regularly. Love YGF Malatang in the University District! As someone who wants to try more hotpot, but is easily intimidated, this casual spot has become a family favorite. The nature of their design makes it easy to try something new, without having to commit to an entire bowl of it.
Upon entering, you‚Äôre invited to pick up a bowl and tongs and select from a wide selection of veggies, seafood, and meats. Fill your bowl with what you know you‚Äôll love and then select a piece or two of something new to you. Your bowl is weighed and you‚Äôre asked to choose a broth and spice level. You pay and are given a number.
You are able to watch them prepare your soup or find a table. When your meal is ready, an automated voice twice says your number. Even at super busy times, it‚Äôs easy to hear. Pick up your bowl and take it to the finishing station to add your personal touches. We‚Äôve done both dine in and take-away and it‚Äôs always good!
Parking is street and usually available. It‚Äôs also just a quick walk from U-Dist Light Rail.

We tried the Beef Bone Broth soup and absolutely enjoyed it! Super flavorful and perfect with one scoop of chili oil as well. There was a wide variety of ingredients to add into our bowl, and it was well organized & clean!

Despite it getting busy when we visited, we got our bowls and to a table really fast! Super fun and delicious place to have a hot bowl of soup filled with anything you‚Äôd like! Highly recommend, and will come again.

reviews.text:
I really enjoyed my experience here! Not the most flavorful Indian food I've ever had, but it's a fusion place so that's what I expected, and for the price I don't think you can beat it.

I got a 6 inch butter chicken sub. It's the biggest 6 inch sandwich I've ever had! The sauce was not the most flavorful, but still tasty, and the bread was perfect (soft on the inside, crispy flaky on the outside), and the chicken itself was cooked very well. There was also a generous amount of cheese, and onion and green bell peppers added a nice touch. For only $7 (before taxes/tips) I don't think I've had such a tasty and filling sandwich.

Afterwards I decided to get ice cream. They have a good selection of Western and Indian flavors. I wanted to try all of them, but could only eat a bit, so I ordered one scoop. But for the price of one he gave me two!

Also I saw previous reviews mentioned there was no water? But currently they offer both bottled and cup water. And for me the service was very fast, and the man behind the counter was so nice.

The one recommendation I have for the place would be to play some music. When I visited there was no music and very few people. I think they should be more popular, though!

Really disappointing experience. Service was painfully slow, and the staff seemed uninterested. When the food finally arrived, it was underwhelming. One dish even had a hair in it ‚Äî completely unacceptable and raises serious hygiene concerns.

I ordered the Bombay vegetarian sandwich expecting something flavorful and known taste. What I got was just cheese and olives slapped between bread with a tiny piece of capsicum ‚Äî no spice, no chutney, no vegetables. It felt lazy and totally disconnected from what the name promised.

There was no drinking water available ‚Äî not even bottled water for sale. For a restaurant serving food, this is shocking. Even a cooler with water bottles would‚Äôve been better than nothing.

Between the poor service, sub-par food, and lack of basic amenities, this visit was a total letdown. Definitely not worth the time or money, and I won‚Äôt be returning.

The butter marsala curry is herbaceous and absolutely delicious. The garlic paneer has the right kind of garlic flavor and is just the right amount of umami. Will be coming back for lunches again in the near future!

Did a call in order, got the Indo-Chinese fusion "chili chicken sub" which is a bit of a misnomer because that makes you think that it has chili like beans chili. The dosa was really tasty, crispy and the masala was flavorful. The Batura was fluffy, but the chole was mid, not very masaledar, it was not that spicy or well seasoned as we requested. Amazing authentic atmosphere, it reminds me of being invited into a welcoming home kitchen.
